runs.comm: length ball wide enough outside off for White to swing at, he gets it over cover but not timed well enough to get it to the rope
better line and Finch plays forward up on the off side
touch straight and clipped out to deep square leg - very short boundary that side, 60 yards at best
fuller length on off stump, pushed forward up on the off side
good length just outside off, it nips back a little and beats the loose prod to cover of White who's beaten on the inside edge
good length on off stump, White knocks it down towards cover
back of a length slower ball on off stump, Finch stays inside it and guides it behind point for a single
firm drive on the up to the right of mid-off, Broad is down to half-save very smartly with a dive
straighter line, blocked coming forward up towards point
White stepped to leg, Dernbach followed him and tucks him up well, White can only fend to midwicket
another step to leg, this time White frees himself up nicely and swings a length ball over square leg into the building site
full at the stumps, played forward to midwicket
full at the off stump and Finch swings it down the ground, lovely clean strike into the stands, dead straight
better length and Finch forced into blocking around the off stump
full on off stump and driven out to long-on who's gone back
full length on off stump, blocked up to mid-on

full length outside off, driven without moving his feet, clean outside edge, straight to Root who drops the chance and it was a sitter in all fairness, little movement down to his right knee and it went straight through his hands
full at the stumps, flicked wide of mid-on for a quick single
slides down the leg side with White giving himself room
length ball, clipped into midwicket for an easy single
just back of a length at the stumps, just blocked in the crease
shorter, goes to pull but was cramped up with Bresnan following Finch shuffling to leg, gets hit on the shoulder
full at the stumps, slower ball, picked up beautifully over midwicket, just a little clip and almost into the building site again
drags the length back slightly, pushed into the covers and a quick single
very full on off stump, White steps to leg and tries to swing it down the ground, gets it low on the bat to mid-on
little width outside off and guided backward of square to third man
fuller length, Finch swings through the line again and finds cow corner, largely clubbed that
swings again and goes straight over the bowler's head, better timing on this and over the advertising hoarding it goes
slower ball on off stump, dabbed into the covers and they race a single
forward press just outside off, finds cover
slower ball full toss but it nearly deceives White who gets a thick inside edge to short long leg
step to leg, Bresnan follows him on a length, gets pushed wide of mid-on
length on off stump, dabbed into the covers for another quick single
turned through square leg this time
full length on the stumps, tucked to midwicket
back foot firm punch wide enough of point for a single
tapped into the off side and finds cover
full toss on the stumps, clipped past short long leg, poor ball
very full at the off stumps, played firmly to extra cover who can only fumble
length ball at the stumps, swung over the leg side and just evades deep-square leg, only just
slower ball at the off stump, just blocked back to the bowler
slower ball on the stumps again, this is worked wide of the bowler and they get a quick single
length just outside off, guided to short third man and there's no run available
White steps to leg and slips a little trying a violent swing to the off side, finds cover
steps down and lifts this over cover, on the bounce to the sweeper
back and crashed from off stump through point, beats the sweeper to the rope
fuller length and Finch smashes this up and over extra cover, nailed
full length at middle and leg, tucked through square leg, they push for two but it's not on
dabbed reverse sweep, bit of an edge but gets it very fine and it skips away to the boundary
slower ball outside off, called wide but it was inside the guideline outside off and Finch was simply done in the flight
shorter length, chopped from off stump to short third man
back of a length, pulled hard over midwicket and evades deep-midwicket
hard swing to leg, along the floor to deep-midwicket this time
slower ball, forward on the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
back of a length, chopped wide of deep cover, they get back for two and Finch gets fifty
fuller at the stumps, driven back to the bowler off high on the bat
full length on the stumps, flourishing swing through the line, opens the face and whacks it wide of long-off, fabulous stroke
over the wicket now, flat delivery, placed wide enough of deep-midwicket for a couple
similar delivery, worked too close to the deep-midwicket this time
leg side delivery, Finch tries to slog sweep and misses
length delivery, worked out to deep-square leg
full length on the stumps, an unusual slap across the line and works it past short long leg and gets four, 100 up
tossed up and pushed out to deep-midwicket but Bopara is too slow coming in and it's two more and fifty for White
full length wide of off stump, Finch had stepped to leg and was well away from it
full length at the stumps, forced down to long-on
full toss on the stumps, tried to be swung to leg, totally miscued off the splice but it's hit so badly it falls well short of long-on running in
but this carries to long-on as Finch swung hard at a length ball, aiming at the leg side and didn't get it anywhere near the middle, straight to Hales who took a solid catch
delicately ran down fine past  short third man, deft touch from just outside off
full at the stumps, driven to long-on
leg stump line, careful push out to long-on
goes for the reverse sweep first ball and was lucky to get some glove on that in front of all three, it rebounds to point and they get a quick single
plays forward and runs it in between the two deep leg side fielders
full outside leg stump and ran to deep-square leg
forward and gets hit on the pad flicking to leg
down the leg side for a wide, sharp take from Buttler
goes for the slog sweep and it hits the pad and runs not far enough away from Buttler for a leg bye
steps to leg and heaves a length ball across the line onto the bank over midwicket
cutter on the stumps and White manages to steer it backward of square, unlucky for the bowler that
full a foot outside off, slapped wide of long-on, excellent placement, timed well too

full toss wide of off stump, swung at and it comes off a huge top edge and short long leg comes in and takes the catch but the bowler's end umpire has called no-ball on height, I'm not too sure about that, they're not even checking upstairs. Or maybe they are now asking for the third umpire, which makes perfect sense, it's close but plenty of these are ruled okay. Rule is standing position in the crease to judge on these things. But the third umpire is sticking with the on-field call
length on the stumps, tried to be swung to leg and gets a toe end into the leg side for a single

full and straight, White swings hard across the line, huge appeal for lbw and given out England needed that badly. Looks pretty straight and struck the pad low, so it looks likely that would have hit leg stump, Hawk Eye has it only clipping but the real time shot looked good
full on the stumps, pressed into midwicket for an easy single
length at the stumps, tucked to point stepping back
down the track, worked to short long leg and they take a sharp single
reverse sweep from outside leg and gets enough bat to clear point
goes again and this is nailed over cover for six! Pietersen-esque! Nails the reverse slog sweep into the stands, amazing shot
leg side wide
full on leg stump, clipped to deep-midwicket, they take on Bopara for the second and get home comfortably
conventional sweep this time and finds the gap backward of square
forward just outside off, dabbed into the covers for a single
full length wide of off stump, tried to be carved off the back foot but misses
straighter and dabbed into square leg for a quick single
length outside off, pushed to short third man for a quick single
full at the off stump, a huge heave to leg brings an inside edge that doesn't carry through to Buttler
length ball on off stump, dabbed into the covers for a single

full on the stumps, goes to reverse slog sweep and chips it to point easy catch for Bresnan. Horrible shot really, he never gets his head down enough does Maxwell. Back of the hand delivery from Bopara does the trick, Maxwell never got under the full delivery
full length turned into the leg side, just a single
back of a length at the body, Bailey misses with a pull
full at the stumps, forced down the ground off an inside edge, just a single
similar length delivery, tried to be pushed up the wicket but only finds the bowler this time
length just outside off, pressed to cover
length at the stumps, a stand and deliver smash straight over the bowler's head
better length, this is forced down to long-off
full length wide of off stump, reached for and chipped just short of extra cover
yorker length wide of off stump, too wide this time
full at the stumps, forced down the ground and just one to long-on
full just outside off, steered wide of third man for a couple
full again, driven out to deep cover
full following Bailey who stepped to leg and misses, Buttler makes an excellent diving save and nearly gets up to run out Lynn
slower ball on a length outside off, slapped off the toe of the bat back to the bowler
full at leg stump, driven back to the bowler, well saved from Dernbach
length ball, Lynn steps to leg and swings it into the building site, nailed it. But the length was simply the wrong one
full toss at the body, Lynn gloves it down the leg side and it runs for four, definitely a no ball on height but byes given! I don't think so
yorker at the stumps, forced back to the bowler
steps across the line and swings to leg, not struck properly and a good job for Lynn because it lands in front of deep-square leg running in
full outside off, swung down the ground off a thick inside edge to long-off, they take on the fielder and get back for two, Bailey doesn't want the bowling
yorker length just inside the guideline offside off - I love that delivery - tried to be chopped away but missed
just misses the length and gets whacked over long-off, lovely clean hit
full and wide, reached for and gets a toe-end out to deep cover
low full toss and Bailey finally times one, clubbing this wide of mid-on
full and wide, reached for again and gets a toe end to cover, 200 up
full delivery outside off out of the back of the hand, swung hard at and gets it straight up in the air and Bresnan takes the catch at point
full at the stumps, swung down the ground, they sprint and nick a second of long-on
full at the stumps, Lynn steps to the off side and paddle sweeps, gets it over the 45 and that runs away for four, lovely touch
right up there again, tries to play straight and forces it back to the bowler, they steal a single
steps right across the line and takes a length ball behind square on the leg side, somehow forces it between keeper and the 45
swept hard and gets it between deep-midwicket and deep-square leg for a couple
